so complicated?

118
00:06:25,840 --> 00:06:27,478
-Dr. Cooper?
-Yes.

119
00:06:27,679 --> 00:06:30,432
I'm Special Agent Page, FBI.

120
00:06:33,120 --> 00:06:36,669
You say you're Special Agent Page,
FBI.

121
00:06:36,880 --> 00:06:38,472
Here's my ID.

122
00:06:38,639 --> 00:06:43,190
And here is my Justice League
membership card.

123
00:06:45,279 --> 00:06:47,315
But that doesn't prove
I know Batman.

124
00:06:48,600 --> 00:06:51,876
I just wanna ask you a few questions
about Howard Wolowitz.

125
00:06:52,480 --> 00:06:54,948
Oh.Well, all right.

126
00:06:55,480 --> 00:06:57,596
I doubt anyone would risk
the stiff penalties...

127
00:06:57,760 --> 00:07:00,228
...for impersonating a federal officer
just to ask questions...

128
00:07:00,399 --> 00:07:04,187
...about a minor-league engineer
with an unresolved Oedipal complex.

129
00:07:05,359 --> 00:07:08,988
-Thank you.
-For the record, I truly support the FBI...

130
00:07:09,160 --> 00:07:12,038
...in the mission
which is expressed through their motto.

131
00:07:12,239 --> 00:07:14,594
Fidelity, bravery, integrity?

132
00:07:14,799 --> 00:07:16,630
Correct. Now to business.

133
00:07:17,239 --> 00:07:21,232
Eighteen years ago,
I sent the FBI Crime Lab samples...

134
00:07:21,399 --> 00:07:24,948
...from a bag of excrement that had
been lit on fire on my front porch...

135
00:07:26,959 --> 00:07:30,269
...for fingerprinting and DNA analysis.

136
00:07:30,440 --> 00:07:32,271
Why haven't I heard back yet?

137
00:07:32,760 --> 00:07:36,548
Well, the FBI Crime Lab
does have a lot on its plate.

138
00:07:36,760 --> 00:07:40,150
That's of little comfort to a nation
attempting to scrape burning feces...

139
00:07:40,319 --> 00:07:41,638
...off its shoes.

140
00:07:42,320 --> 00:07:44,675
Would you mind
if we talked about Mr. Wolowitz now?

141
00:07:45,280 --> 00:07:47,350
A little, but go on.

142
00:07:47,519 --> 00:07:48,793
Thank you.

143
00:07:48,960 --> 00:07:51,076
Would you characterize him
as responsible?

144
00:07:52,600 --> 00:07:54,716
I'm going to answer that
with a visual aid.

145
00:07:56,600 --> 00:08:00,991
This is my nine-disc complete
Lord of the Rings trilogy Blu-ray set.

146
00:08:01,200 --> 00:08:02,918
Mr. Wolowitz borrowed it...

147
00:08:03,079 --> 00:08:07,197
...damaged plastic-retention
hub number three...

148
00:08:10,760 --> 00:08:13,399
...and then returned it to me
hoping I wouldn't notice.

149
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:16,996
Would you characterize that
as responsible?

150
00:08:17,200 --> 00:08:19,794
That's really not the sort of thing
we're interested in.

151
00:08:20,679 --> 00:08:24,433
-You heard me say "Blu-ray," right?
-I did.

152
00:08:25,239 --> 00:08:27,878
Very well,
would you be interested in knowing...

153
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:31,669
...that Mr. Wolowitz once snuck
on to my "World of Warcraft" account...

154
00:08:31,839 --> 00:08:34,512
...and changed the name
of a certain level-80 warlock...

155
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:37,513
...from "Sheldor" to "Smeldor"?

156
00:08:38,079 --> 00:08:41,151
I'm afraid not. Is there anything else?

157
00:08:41,360 --> 00:08:43,430
Anything else?
Where would you like to start?

158
00:08:43,600 --> 00:08:46,558
He refuses to pay fines when
he's overdue with books I lend him.

159
00:08:46,719 --> 00:08:49,677
He crashed the Mars Rover
while attempting to impress a woman.

160
00:08:49,879 --> 00:08:52,473
He recommended that I go see
the third Matrix movie...

161
00:08:52,640 --> 00:08:56,315
...because it was, and I quote,
"Just as good as the first one."

162
00:08:57,120 --> 00:09:00,237
If that's not irresponsible,
I don't know what is.

163
00:09:00,439 --> 00:09:01,952
The Mars Rover?

164
00:09:07,959 --> 00:09:10,268
-Did I say "Mars Rover"?
-You did.

165
00:09:10,840 --> 00:09:12,831
That was actually
a poorly chosen example...

166
00:09:12,999 --> 00:09:15,149
...as it had nothing to do with me.

167
00:09:15,360 --> 00:09:18,989
-Yes, well, let's talk about it anyway.
-I don't want to.

168
00:09:20,120 --> 00:09:22,429
Not that my disinclination
to discuss the topic...

169
00:09:22,600 --> 00:09:25,433
...should be interpreted as evidence
of Howard Wolowitz's culpability...

170
00:09:25,600 --> 00:09:28,592
...in the destruction of government
property worth millions of dollars.

171
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:31,360
Thank you, Dr. Cooper.
I think I have all I need.

172
00:09:31,560 --> 00:09:33,551
Oh, good.

173
00:09:33,720 --> 00:09:37,474
l was afraid you were going to fixate
on that Mars Rover incident.

174
00:09:42,600 --> 00:09:43,953
Hey, buddies.

175
00:09:44,120 --> 00:09:47,476
Guess who didn't get security clearance
to work on the giant space laser.

176
00:09:47,639 --> 00:09:50,278
-What happened?
-Background interviews didn't go well.

177
00:09:50,480 --> 00:09:52,994
You guys wouldn't know anything
about that, would you?

178
00:09:55,080 --> 00:09:58,436
Well, actually, I may have gotten
a little tipsy when I talked to her.

179
00:09:59,840 --> 00:10:01,478
And I may have hit on her a little bit.

180
00:10:01,640 --> 00:10:02,675
[HOWARD SCOFFS]

181
00:10:02,840 --> 00:10:05,354
And I may have thrown up rum cake
on her shoes.

182
00:10:06,800 --> 00:10:09,872
I see. Well, it's good to know
when I need you guys...

183
00:10:10,080 --> 00:10:13,595
...I can always count on you
to step up and ruin everything.

184
00:10:15,639 --> 00:10:17,550
-| feel awful.
-Me too.

185
00:10:17,759 --> 00:10:20,796
I thought if anyone was gonna
screw things up for Howard...

186
00:10:20,959 --> 00:10:22,517
...it'd be Sheldon.

187
00:10:23,040 --> 00:10:26,510
Well, your expectations
have been subverted.

188
00:10:26,759 --> 00:10:27,794
Ha, ha.

189
00:10:34,759 --> 00:10:36,317
What are you doing up?

190
00:10:36,520 --> 00:10:38,351
Sleep eludes me, Leonard.

191
00:10:38,560 --> 00:10:39,629
Really?

192
00:10:39,800 --> 00:10:42,109
Maybe sleep has met you before.

193
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:45,240
Mockery? That's all you have to offer?

194
00:10:45,439 --> 00:10:47,748
-Sorry. Why can't you sleep?
-Who knows?

195
00:10:47,920 --> 00:10:50,434
I haven't watched
any scary movies recently.

196
00:10:50,600 --> 00:10:53,068
I'm no longer obsessing
over why the predicted mass...

197
00:10:53,240 --> 00:10:56,835
...of the quantum vacuum has little
effect on the expansion of the universe.

198
00:10:56,999 --> 00:11:00,275
And it's been weeks since I took
that accidental sip of Red Bull.

199
00:11:01,080 --> 00:11:03,435
Something happen today
that's bothering you?

200
00:11:03,639 --> 00:11:07,427
Well, I did mention the Mars Rover
incident to that FBI agent...

201
00:11:07,600 --> 00:11:10,034
...and probably cost Howard
his security clearance.

202
00:11:10,240 --> 00:11:12,959
-What?
-Yeah, but why should that keep me up?

203
00:11:13,560 --> 00:11:14,993
Because you feel guilty?

204
00:11:15,759 --> 00:11:17,192
Interesting.

205
00:11:17,360 --> 00:11:21,239
So you're saying my insomnia
is caused by a guilty conscience?

206
00:11:21,439 --> 00:11:24,192
Actually, you don't have insomnia.
You're sleeping now.

207
00:11:24,400 --> 00:11:27,312
-Excuse me?
-You're having a guilt-ridden dream.

208
00:11:27,520 --> 00:11:29,909
Do you have any evidence
to support that hypothesis?

209
00:11:30,120 --> 00:11:32,315
How about that Gorn
sitting on the couch?

210
00:11:36,160 --> 00:11:38,720
That seems fairly conclusive.

211
00:11:38,920 --> 00:11:41,639
No, Gorn, no.

212
00:11:42,319 --> 00:11:44,594
That's where I sit.

213
00:11:46,439 --> 00:11:49,078
Thank you for agreeing to see me,
Agent Page.

214
00:11:49,280 --> 00:11:52,829
Thank you for filing a complaint
with my superior, Dr. Cooper.

215
00:11:54,039 --> 00:11:57,236
I understand you wanna recant
your statement about Howard Wolowitz?

216
00:11:57,439 --> 00:12:00,112
-Yes.
-Was your statement untrue?

217
00:12:00,280 --> 00:12:01,349


218
00:12:02,360 --> 00:12:04,430
