219
00:12:04,639 --> 00:12:08,427
I'm sorry,
I don't recall you saying no backsies.

220
00:12:09,840 --> 00:12:11,159
Is there anything else?

221
00:12:11,360 --> 00:12:13,828
Yes, I'd like to offer
a laudatory statement...

222
00:12:13,999 --> 00:12:17,469
...about Howard's many excellent
qualities I believe will tip the scales...

223
00:12:17,639 --> 00:12:20,358
...back in his favor. Ahem.
"Howard Joel Wolowitz.

224
00:12:20,520 --> 00:12:23,796
H is for 'honesty,'
of which he has much.

225
00:12:23,960 --> 00:12:26,349
O is for 'outstanding,' which he is such.

226
00:12:26,519 --> 00:12:28,953
W is for 'witty.' He's quick with a joke.

227
00:12:29,120 --> 00:12:30,997
A is for 'artistic,' his ability--"

228
00:12:31,199 --> 00:12:33,872
I'm sorry, Dr. Cooper,
this matter is already closed.

229
00:12:34,080 --> 00:12:36,833
But I still have "ard Joel Wolowitz"
left to go.

230
00:12:37,319 --> 00:12:38,877
It's closed.

231
00:12:40,440 --> 00:12:43,113
I don't understand why you people
are picking on my friend Howard...

232
00:12:43,279 --> 00:12:45,747
...when there are much more serious
security threats to pursue.

233
00:12:45,919 --> 00:12:47,796
For instance,
when I first met Leonard...

234
00:12:47,959 --> 00:12:51,554
...he was on the verge of giving away
rocket secrets to a North Korean spy...

235
00:12:51,720 --> 00:12:54,314
...and not one agent
ever investigated that.

236
00:12:54,720 --> 00:12:57,109
This is Leonard Hofstadter?

237
00:12:57,920 --> 00:13:01,230
No, it's a different Leonard.
He's Chinese, red hair, six fingers.

238
00:13:01,399 --> 00:13:02,388
Goodbye.

239
00:13:06,079 --> 00:13:08,547
Raj, have you seen Howard?

240
00:13:08,759 --> 00:13:10,556
I think he's eating lunch.

241
00:13:10,759 --> 00:13:13,114
Uh, Sheldon, I want you to meet
Neil DeGrasse Tyson...

242
00:13:13,280 --> 00:13:14,952
...from the Hayden Planetarium
in New York.

243
